This is a demo using DZT shoptify monitor

github : https://github.com/dzt/shopify-monitor
Youtube tutorial : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rpO5wdudfpQ&feature=youtu.be

Dependencies
------------
1. Node JS (npm command)
2. Mongodb
3. git
4. homebrew ( brew )

Steps:  1. Install NodeJS manually from website https://nodejs.org/en/
	2. Install Mongodb by 
	   brew install mongodb
	3. mkdir shoptify-monitor-demo & cd inside
        4. Git clone https://github.com/dzt/shopify-monitor
	5. sudo npm install
	6. mv config.example.json config.json
	7. brew services start mongodb on WINDOW 1
	8. node server on WINDOW 2
	9. open up a web browser to further down configuration & monitoring


